  "section_name": "Financial Analysis",
  "text": "Apple's research and development (R&D) expenses were $34.6 billion in fiscal year 2025, representing a 10.0% increase from $31.4 billion in fiscal year 2024 and a 12.2% increase from $29.9 billion in fiscal year 2023. This investment intensity, measured as a percentage of revenue, was 8.3% in fiscal year 2025, up from 8.0% in fiscal year 2024 and 7.6% in fiscal year 2023. The increasing R&D intensity suggests that Apple is committed to innovation and maintaining its competitive edge in technology-driven markets. Despite the rising R&D costs, the company's profitability metrics remain strong, indicating effective resource allocation.",
